fields.description: Handcrafted from 100% reclaimed teak and finished with a stunning mocha color. This contemporary 6-Drawer Dresser looks so put together with it's golden handles that standout like buttons on a navy coat.
fields.material_description: 100% Solid Reclaimed Teak and Reclaimed Steel Base/Drawer Hardware

fields.description: We fell in love with the grain of the wood, the straight lines, and especially the feet on this dresser. Sustainable (with with reclaimed wood) and handcrafted, this is a one of a kind piece.
fields.material_description: 100% Solid Reclaimed Teak Wood and Soft closing drawer slide technology

fields.description: The warm and elegant grain of the Teak wood is a stand-out feature... and did we mention that it's made of 100% reclaimed wood and handcrafted! Designed with soft closing drawer tracks, it allows the wood to speak for itself. What's more we love the mid-century design of this 9 drawer piece.
fields.material_description: 100% Solid Reclaimed Teak and Soft Closing Drawer Tracks

fields.description: Gorgeous mid-century side table made from 100% reclaimed wood and handcrafted! Each of the 3 drawers leverage soft closing technology, allowing the wood to speak for itself. The warm and elegant grain of the Teak wood is a stand-out feature.
fields.material_description: 100% Solid Reclaimed Teak and Soft Closing Drawer Tracks

fields.description: We love the interesting look of this shingled, 6-drawer dresser. It's natural honey color finish is so sweet. Remember, no two pieces will be alike. This is handcrafted and made of 100% reclaimed teak.
fields.material_description: 100% Solid Reclaimed Teak Wood and Touch Drawer Tracks

fields.description: We love the assymmetrical look of this 3-Drawer 1-Door End Table.  This piece is artisan crafted with meticulous care. Each piece has a different wood variation, which helps to make each item unique.
fields.material_description: 100% Solid Reclaimed Teak and Soft Closing Door Hinges and Drawer Tracks

fields.description: The reclaimed teak used in this piece was salvaged from a 100 year old home that was being demolished. It was reconstructed into this beautiful 2 level cocktail table. Handcrafted and with a natural honey color finish. Bring a piece of history home.
Modern, shingled credenza made from reclaimed teak. Has 2 touch door hinges and 3 drawers that incorporate soft closing technology. Handcrafted so every item is unique.
fields.material_description: 100% Solid Reclaimed Teak and Touch Door Hinges and Drawer Tracks

fields.description: Mid-Century Modern media cabinet. It has three soft closing drawers, and two solid wood doors each with two shelves to ensure ample storage space. Made by hand, with 100% reclaimed teak.
fields.material_description: 100% Solid Reclaimed Teak Wood. Three soft closing drawers, and two solid wood doors each with two shelves to ensure ample storage space.

fields.description: It's as cool as James Dean. We're convinced that's how this coffee table got its name. Unique shape. Handcrafted (of course). Made from 100% reclaimed wood. You really can't get any better than that. No 2 pieces are alike.

Grounded, conveying the strength of a rooted tree. We like the stature of this coffee table. It tends to draw the eye. What's more appealing is that it is made out of 100% reclaimed wood -- yes, eco-friendly, sustainable, all of that good stuff. It's also hand made so that no two pieces are exactly alike.

Artisan crafted with meticulous care. Given its handmade and hand-finished nature, variations in the wood is to be expected and celebrated. The reclaimed Teak used in this piece is approximately 100 years old, and was salvaged from a house being demolished.

Each item is unique and no two are exactly alike

Fans available for an additional $100 each (up to 2)
fields.material_description: 100% Solid Reclaimed Teak. One soft closing drawer, and two soft closing solid wood doors each with a center shelf to ensure ample storage space to fit all of your media needs.

fields.description: The reclaimed Teak used in this piece is approximately 100 years old, and was salvaged from a house being demolished. The reclaimed steel used was salvaged from a 1940′s ship. This side table has a natural honey color finish complimented with gold colored base. We love it's unique architecture. This piece is handcrafted.
fields.color_description: Natural Honey complimented with gold colored base
fields.material_description: 100% Solid Reclaimed Teak Wood Top & Reclaimed Steel Base

fields.description: There's something gorgeous about the simplicity of this table. We love the splayed legs at the bottom and how they come strongly together in the middle (what sturdy construction). Made from 100 year old teak, which was reclaimed. Handcrafted.
Nice and simple, mid-century modern dining table. It has gorgeous splayed legs and a beautiful teak grain. Handcrafted and made from reclaimed wood.
We liked these teak dining table chairs because of the intricate panelling on the seat. Sustainable (100% reclaimed teak) and modern, these are a great pick.

A nice, simple dining chair. We like the 2 slats in the back contrasted with the full slab of teak for the seat. Nicely constructed -- handmade in fact. Also, did we mention that the teak is reclaimed? So, you're sure to get a one of a kind piece every time.
Functional and modern, the round shape works well with a variety of sectionals and sofa sizes. Made with reclaimed wood, so each table top has a unique grain and look... as well as its own story.
Made from recycled Elm. The table pairs the warmth of aged wood with darkened metal frames for a perfectly imperfect industrial look.

The right mix of wood and metal, this is the foundation of the industrial look. This piece is simple yet stylish. Made from mixed recycled hardwoods, the weathered feel brings warmth and nostalgia to a space.
fields.material_description:
100% Reclaimed lumber.
Polyurethane finish over painted surface.

fields.description: Nesting tables - not new but new in popularity. Why? Function, function, function. They are a space-saving solution (which is key for city living and small spaces). These wooden nesting tables have a sleek design but also a classical charm.

The right mix of wood and metal, this is the foundation of the industrial look. Made from 100% reclaimed wood. Although it is simple in design, this table brings a modern edge (and we're not just saying that because it's square).

This piece tends to draw you in. It is in some ways tantalizing... perhaps it is the beautiful pattern on the wood that attracts ones eyes to the center. The warm wood, in contrast with the silver base, creates a beautiful tension that entices you to stare longer.
This wood and metal bench is inspired by the post industrial era. Long, thick planks of recycled wood are fused together on top a metal base. Add an industrial touch to your living or dining space.

Talk about unforgettable. Show off your style with this reclaimed dresser. The original wood shines through in a variety of hues, like brush strokes that flow and whirl around one another. It's enough to bring life to any room. (does not come with wheels as pictured). Maintain the piece with Howard Orange Oil approximately once a month.
fields.material_description:
Polyurethane finish over painted surface.
100% Reclaimed lumber.

fields.description: Made with Kerr... oops, we mean care. This is a beautiful round coffee table with a top made of recycled wood. The crossed legs add a touch of elegance to the piece.
What a solid piece! Made from recycled Elm, its rustic and has a whole lot of character. The color of the recycled wood will vary from piece to piece, but that's part of what makes it so unique.

This piece was crafted with a lot of passion. It's body made from reclaimed wood. It's beauty shines through in a variety of hues, like brush strokes that flow and whirl around one another. It's enough to bring life to any room. Maintain with Howard Orange Oil (approx once a month or so).
fields.material_description:
Polyurethane finish over painted surface.
100% Reclaimed lumber.

fields.description: Hide your delicate items and show off your style with this reclaimed dresser. It stands tall, dressed in strokes of colors that flow and whirl around one another to bring life to any room. Use it in a bedroom to store clothes and accessories, or stand it in a child's room to store tiny socks and small clothing Maintain with Howard Orange Oil (approx once a month or so).
fields.material_description:
Polyurethane finish over painted surface.
100% Reclaimed lumber.

fields.description: You might be surprised to learn that a new material is overtaking granite as the most popular choice for kitchen design -- quartz. It's durable, low maintenance as well as beautiful. This kitchen set has a gorgeous rose quartz top and eye-catching angles at its base.

This piece is certainly a gem.  Made from reclaimed wood, the distinctive grain differs from table to table. The natural nicks and knots to exude character. It's supported by pipe legs to further the industrial look.
This crank table is an industrial aesthetic with a unique blend of iron. Utilizing a variety of refurbished materials, each evocative piece is inspired by the object’s original use.
Oozing with industrial goodness, this crank table creates the perfect atmosphere. Set down a cold drink or gathering around the table with friends for a quick bite and a little gossip.

Yup, we're star-gazing. Our favorite aspect of this piece are the beautiful criss crosses at the base of the table. They resemble the bottom half of a star. It's a nice ornament that balances the character of the wood (100% reclaimed), which garners its own attention.

You may want to place this piece next to the wall, but it certainly isn't any wall flower. It'll garner attention. Think of it as a the strong silent type. With 16 drawers, it'll hold any secret..  it'll hold your knicks and your knacks too. Made from mixed recycled hardwoods, expect the color to vary. Maintain with Howard Orange Oil (approx once a month or so).
fields.material_description:
Polyurethane finish over painted surface.
100% Reclaimed lumber.

This rare Danish modern mid century lounge chair is a hold out of the 
space age.  A Kagan-esque biomorphic teak frame supports a floating 
contoured fiberglass seat bucket that forms to the body effortlessly. 
 Newly recovered in crimson wool from Kvadrat’s Tonica collection with 
fresh foam, this chair will make a perfect addition to any mid century 
collection.  Solid teak frame is in excellent original condition with 
typical wear for its vintage
fields.material_description: wood frame wool covered seat and back

fields.description:
This wonderful Danish modern rocking chair comes directly from the 
estate of a 1950s Danish movie star.  Highly sculptural, this piece is a
 fantastic investment for
 any mid century collector.  All wood surfaces have been reinforced and 
refinished to their original specifications.  Seat retains its original 
crimson wool upholstery, which is in excellent condition

Wonderful Danish teak reading table by H.M.N. This Läsbord, or reading table, is perfect for holding books, computers, serving, or as a low- profile storage table. Large teak tray pivots while the small side tray stays stationary. The chrome base features wheels as well as an extendable stem. In excellent original condition with typical wear for its vintage.

Designed by Victor Wilkins in the 1960s, this fantastic dresser features
 four deep drawers with solid teak drawer fronts carved afromosia pulls.
  The size is perfect for pairing with any modern bedframe as 
nightstands or great for general storage.  In excellent original 
condition with typical wear for its vintage

Danish modern biomorphic mid century coffee table in teak by Hugo Troeds
 Bjärnum.  Beautiful organically formed teak slab rests upon three, 
black tipped legs.  In good original condition with typical wear for its
 vintage.
fields.short_name: Hugo Troeds Bjarnum Biomorphic  Coffee Table

fields.description:
This amazing mid century modern small teak telephone bench was designed 
and manufactured by Chippy Telephone Seats of England.  Perfect for any 
modern entry or hallway, this lovely piece features a pullout seat 
covered in original nubby tangerine wool.  An open compartment below and
 a drawer above provide plenty of storage storage.  Original pullout 
“memory slide” offers a place to store names + numbers, with a built in 
pencil holder! In excellent original condition with typical wear for its
 vintage
fields.short_name: Small Mid Century Chippy Telephone Bench

fields.description:
English modern G Plan Fresco double dresser.  Designed by Victor Wilkins
 in the 1960s, this fantastic dresser features eight deep drawers with 
solid teak drawer fronts carved afromosia pulls.  With its low design, 
this piece is perfect for any space.  In excellent original condition 
with typical wear for its vintage.

This set of eight mid century dining chairs in mahogany was manufactured by Younger in the 1960s. These will pair perfectly with any vintage or modern table, and feature subtly curved, tall ergonomic backs, which lend to hours of comfortable dining for those long dinner parties and holidays. Seat bottoms have been newly upholstered with fresh foam, and recovered in heather grey Kvadrat wool. Frames are in excellent original condition with typical wear for their vintage
fields.short_name: Divani sectional Sofa with Built-In iPod/iPhone dock

fields.description: Danish modern drop leaf bar cart in teak. The perfect server, this versatile piece features a functional drop leaf system that allows for a quick transformation when a larger table top is needed. Two lateral drawers extend out of each side providing necessary storage. Fixed lower shelf provides additional storage for bottles. Piece is situated on smooth gliding original brass casters. In excellent original condition

Danish modern mid century draw leaf extension coffee table in teak + oak designed by Børge Mogensen. A beautiful teak slab floats atop oak legs for a striking contrast. Keep it closed for regular use, and easily extend the usable surface to almost double size when entertaining. Recently refinished and in excellent condition.
fields.short_name: Borge Mogensen Drop Leaf Coffee Table

fields.description: Set of absolutely gorgeous Danish modern mid century nesting tables in teak and oak designed by Svend Madsen. With old growth, rich grain throughout the solid teak tops, these tables float delicately above braced oak legs. A fantastic compliment to any modern decor. Recently refinished and in excellent condition.
fields.short_name: Set of Danish Modern Nesting Tables

fields.description: Danish modern four drawer gentleman’s chest in teak. Extremely well crafted, this piece is wonderful storage solution for any modern home. In excellent original condition with typical wear for its vintage.
fields.short_name: Danish Modern Four Drawer Gentlemans Chest

fields.description: Danish modern mid century six drawer bow front teak highboy dresser. Exceptional build quality throughout. With its wide design and deep drawers, this piece is perfect for any modern bedroom. In excellent original condition with typical wear for its vintage

English modern mid century six drawer dresser / vanity in walnut + rosewood. Hand carved rosewood oval drawer pulls add a wonderful touch to this classic piece. With deeper drawers on the bottom, this piece is perfect for all of your storage needs. Also included is a detachable articulating vanity mirror (not pictured), which can be easily removed for use as a dresser only. In excellent original condition with typical wear for its vintage.

This Danish modern mid century mahogany armoire is a rare find. Perched on tapered spindle legs, this handsome and elegant piece is the perfect storage solution for modern living spaces without ample closet storage. Two large doors open to a large interior with a clothing rack and a hat hook. Comes with original key+ lock. In excellent original condition with typical wear for its vintage.

Danish modern mid century vanity in teak. Designed by Arne Vodder in the 1960s, this beautiful piece is mounted four tapered, spindled legs. Top drawer flips up, revealing a vanity mirror and divided makeup compartment . In excellent original condition with typical wear for its vintage.

Rare early 1960’s vanity / dressing table in teak. Designed by Alfred Cox for Heals Furniture. Beautifully crafted tapered legs support this walnut and mahogany vanity. Four large drawers sit on the left and right sides with one long center drawer nestled in the center. Atomic patinated brass pulls are sophisticated yet ergonomic. A fully articulating mirror with hinged side- mirrors works as a full time vanity, but is easily removable to turn this lovely piece into a desk or extra dresser in an instant. In excellent original condition with typical wear for its vintage

This Danish modern mid century shoe cabinet in mahogany is a wonderfully unusual storage piece! The slender case features two drop down compartments for keeping shoes organized. In excellent original condition with typical wear for its vintage.

Mid century modern Danish teak dresser is full of hidden surprises! The third drawer pulls out to reveal a flip- up vanity mirror nestled between two cubbies. Lower drawers are adorned with brass pulls for additional storage. The bottom flares at the base for a truly atomic look. In excellent original condition with some vintage wear.

This gorgeous Danish modern six drawer mid century highboy dresser is a rare find. Rich woodgrain and high quality construction define this classic piece. In excellent original condition with typical wear for its vintage.

This gorgeous Danish modern mid century bar cart is perfect for apartment living. Occupying a low profile, this lovely cart easily folds out to double in size, making it perfect for hosting. A lower teak framed, removable laminate tray is perfect for preparing and serving cocktails. In excellent original condition.

Fantastic set of six Danish modern highback mid century dining chairs in teak. These will pair perfectly with any vintage or modern table, and feature slightly curved, tall ergonomic backs, which lend to hours of comfortable dining for those long dinner parties and holidays. Seat bottoms have been newly upholstered with fresh foam, and recovered in vintage chartreuse wool. Frames are in excellent original condition with typical wear for their vintage.
fields.short_name: Set of Six Danish Modern Highback Dining Chairs

fields.description: Danish modern mid century sewing cart in teak. Center slide – thru drawer features an interior slider, and is perfect for storing needle + thread. Newly refinished. In excellent condition.

This large Danish modern teak tambour mid century credenza will add a warmth and character to any modern home. Two large tambour doors smoothly glide open to reveal three adjustable shelves, and three center felt lined drawers complete with their original flatware dividers. In excellent original condition with typical wear for its vintage.

This Danish modern mid century “stick back” rocking chair was designed and manufactured by Farstrup Møbler the 1960’s. Constructed in black lacquered oak with a teak seat, this rocker will provide years of comfort. In excellent original condition with typical wear for its vintage.

Danish modern mid century v-legged sewing box in teak. Front drawer drops down to reveal double sliding dividers, with additional storage below. The perfect versatile storage piece for any modern home. Newly refinished. In excellent condition
Pair of Danish modern mid century side tables in teak. Designed by Severin Hansen in the 1960’s. In excellent original condition with typical wear for their vintage.
fields.short_name: Pair of Severin Hansen Side Tables

fields.description: This Danish modern mid century scoop shaped highback lounge chair will make a perfect accent to any modern room. Newly upholstered with fresh foam in grey + claret wool textile from Kvadrat’s Remix collection. In excellent condition.
fields.short_name: Danish Modern Mid Century Highback Scoop Chair
